        <section>
            <p>The following hardware resources are recommended:</p>
            <table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col2" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colnum="2" colwidth="2.32*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">Requirement</entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">Description</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <p>Architecture</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <p>x86_64</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <p>RAM</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <p>At least 32 GB, 64 GB or more recommended. </p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <p>CPU</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <p>At least 8 cores, 16 cores or more recommended.</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <p>Hard disk</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <p>SSD strongly recommended.</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <p>Disk space</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">See below.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <p><ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> without any data requires about 2 GB of disk space. The disk capacity required for log data and metrics data varies considerably depending on the number of services and servers to be monitored.</p>
            <p>Make sure that enough disk space is provided. If required, mount partitions for storing the log data and the metrics data. The default installation uses the following directories:</p>
            <ul id="The_data_directory_of_Elastic_concept_conbody_section_3_ul">
                <li>The data directory of Elasticsearch is located in <codeph>/var/data/elasticsearch</codeph>. ## ${MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT}/elasticsearch/data:/usr/share/elasticsearch/data</li>
                <li>The data directory of InfluxDB is located in <codeph>/var/opt/influxdb/data</codeph>. ##${MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT}/influxdb:/var/lib/influxdb:rw"</li>
                <li>The data directory of MariaDB is located in <codeph>/var/lib/mysql</codeph>. <i>##MariaDB or MySQL? </i> ##${MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT}/mysql:/var/lib/mysql:rw</li>
                <li>The data directory of Kafka is located in <codeph>/var/kafka</codeph>. ##${MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT}/kafka:/data:rw</li>
                <li>The data directory of Grafana is located in <codeph/>. ##${MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT}/grafana/data:/var/lib/grafana/data:rw</li>
            </ul>
            <p><i>in .env file ist variable für mounted volumes:</i></p>
            <p><i> #set base directory for volumes MON_DOCKER_VOL_ROOT=/opt/monasca-containers</i></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Calculating the Required Disk Space</title>
            <p>As a basic rule of thumb, the following formula can be used for calculating the required disk space:</p>
            <p>200 GB + [ number of nodes * retention period * (space for log data/day + space for metrics data/day) ] </p>
            <p>Replace the variables as follows: ##ul compact ##</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Number of nodes corresponds to the number of nodes to be monitored.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Retention period corresponds to 60 days for InfluxDB and Elasticsearch.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Space for log data/day corresponds to approx. 2 GB.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Space for metrics data/day correspond to approx 50 MB.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>The formula is based on the following assumptions for log data: ##ul compact ##</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Approx. 50 log files per node</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Approx. 1 log entry/file/sec </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>200 bytes size</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>The formula is based on the following assumptions for metrics data: ##ul compact ##</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>400 metrics per node </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Time interval: 30 secs </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>20 bytes size</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <note othertype="note">
                <p>Depending on the OpenStack nodes to be monitored there might be additional factors that have an impact on the required disk space, for example, enabling debug logging for one or more OpenStack services.</p>
            </note>
        </section>
